result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher D. Selby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Deliver Illegal Articles to Inmate [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing or ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No contact with A. Trevino directly or indirectly. No phone calls, e-mails, text messages, written communications or by third party. No contact with any State of Wisconsin Correctional Institution unless and inmate in that facility.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Receipt admitted - Reading waived. Infomation has an added charge of Ct 2 - Possession of THC contrary to Wis Stat 961.41(3g)(e). Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Cts 1 & 2 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Repeater enhancer dismissed outright. No statement by DE. Court orders: Ct 1- S/W  2 years probation consecutive to any sentence currently being served including but not limited to Waukesha Co Case No 13CF915 - Conditions: AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing or ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, NC w/ A. Trevino, No contact with any State of Wisconsin Correctional Institution unless an inmate in that facility, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP.
